China and Russia say Pyongyang should be rewarded by the UN Security Council for the measures taken.
U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told the U.N. Security Council on Thursday: “The implementation of the Security Council sanctions must continue vigorously and without interruption until we achieve complete, final and confirmed denuclearization.”
The Security Council has unanimously increased sanctions imposed on North Korea since 2006, in an attempt to block funding for Pyongyang's nuclear and ballistic missile programs.
Pompeo met with Ri in the corridors of the UN General Assembly and later said he would visit Pyongyang again next month to prepare for a second summit.
